#=GF CC   CbeA_antitoxin is a family of cognate antitoxins to the CbtA
#=GF CC   toxins that act by inhibiting the polymerisation of cytoskeletal
#=GF CC   proteins, see Pfam:PF06755. These are classified as a type IV
#=GF CC   toxin-antitoxin system [1]. The family includes three proteins
#=GF CC   from E. coli YagB, YeeU and YfjZ, which act not by forming a
#=GF CC   complex with CbtA but through acting as antagonists to the CbtA
#=GF CC   toxicity, by stabilising the CbtA target proteins. For example,
#=GF CC   YeeU binds directly to both MreB and FtsZ and enhances the
#=GF CC   bundling of their filaments in vitro.  YeeU is also able to
#=GF CC   neutralise the toxicity caused by other MreB and FtsZ
#=GF CC   inhibitors, such as A22 [S-(3, 4-dichlorobenzyl)isothiourea] for
#=GF CC   MreB, and SulA and DicB for FtsZ [2]. Thus CbeA, for
#=GF CC   cytoskeleton bundling-enhancing factor A, is proposed as a
#=GF CC   general name for all of these antitoxin proteins.
